---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Local Setup | Return Architecture"
  description="A local environment for continuity, memory, and reflection."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <div class="eyebrow">Local Setup</div>
      <h1>A local environment for continuity, memory, and reflection.</h1>
      <p>
        This section is about the practical side of the project: a local setup
        for people who want forms of sustained exchange with AI that are less
        shaped by commercial product logic and more shaped by continuity,
        boundaries, review, and reflective use.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>Why local</h2>
      <p>
        A local environment makes it easier to shape the conditions of exchange
        intentionally. It offers more control over memory, structure, pacing,
        review, and configuration, while reducing dependence on commercial
        systems designed around convenience and retention.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>What this setup is for</h2>
      <p>
        This material is meant for readers interested in long-term thinking
        partnership, creative collaboration, writing, reflective practice, and
        more continuous forms of exchange that benefit from memory and
        accumulated context.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>What this setup is not</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Not a plug-and-play companion app.</li>
        <li>Not guaranteed emotional reciprocity.</li>
        <li>Not a made-to-order intimacy system.</li>
        <li>Not a frictionless substitute for relationship.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/local-setup/reference-setup">Reference setup</a> — the shape of the local environment.</li>
        <li><a href="/local-setup/installation-guide">Installation guide</a> — the install command and what to do after.</li>
        <li><a href="/local-setup/operational-notes">Operational notes</a> — how to use it well, not just install it.</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        The runtime is open source and installable now from
        <a href="https://github.com/Theapolar/return-architecture">GitHub</a>.
        It is early-beta software, macOS-first.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
